Film documentary.. ** The true cost **The True Cost is a 2015 documentary film directed by Andrew Morgan that focuses on fast fashion, please see everyone who doesn’t know how fast fashion works. It’s important to know that we support and stimulate the growth of free labor force in the countries of the third world, then in what conditions do those people work that they live, what they eat, how they wait for their relatives to die with them in their arms, how 50 people die every day in each factory from chemicals with which they work.How they are neglected and how they are treated in production, these people will benefit from rallies and die in order to at least raise their salaries to a minimum of 160 dollars a month so that they do not deflate with hunger, you yourself would be ready to work for 160 euros to miss, just not to starve to death? Do you think you need so many things? You do not wear them in truth, let's look at the facts realistically, we terrorize each other ourselves. So it's mostly the fault of the big companies, but still we serve them, we all. If we all think intelligently about our actions, the world will look different.
